<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870305-0036 </DOCNO><HL> Xidex Closes Swiss Disk Plant</HL><DD> 03/05/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> XIDX </IN><DATELINE> PALO ALTO, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Xidex Corp. said it closed its Le Locle, Switzerland, disk-making facility in an economy move that eliminated about 200, or 2.9%, of its 7,000 jobs.    Manufacturing previously done at the Swiss plant will be moved to its Santa Clara, Calif., facilities. Xidex, with $432.3 million of sales in fiscal 1986, ended June 30, makes computer disks and other data storage devices. </TEXT></DOC>